    ],
    "summary": "On April 8, 2015, 1,730 feet of 22 inch casing was dropped to the seafloor from the Noble Sam Croft drillship during drilling operations in Green Canyon 643. The casing connection separated due to an improper connection with a gap of approximately 0.16 inch. The improper connection, combined with 3.3 knot currents, exceeded the load capacity of the connection, causing failure.",
